f=Engineering/nova/operational/skill/nova-skill-routing.md · p=nova's four skills fit together. nova builds mobile app: structured, releasable, verified devices, offline-capable. **nova DORMANT default** whole agent activates `mobile_active` true business actually mobile app). web-only businesses, nova silent work routes mia. · h2:dormant switch (first check, always)=`mobile_active? ── false ──> nova is DORMANT; route to mia (web). Build nothing. \· │ true \· ▼ \· mobile-app-architecture (structure — state, navigation, lifecycle; dated Flutter/framework playbook) \· → offline-sync-discipline (data — offline-first, local persistence, conflict resolution)` · h2:Routing rules (all gated mobile_active)="App structure state navigation platform channel" **mobile-app-architecture**., "Offline local storage sync conflict" **offline-sync-discipline**., "Test devices work iOS/Android" **mobile-verification**., "Release submit staged rollout store review" **app-store-release-discipline**., Web frontend request nova; route **mia**. · h2:Handoffs=**mia**: web frontend; shares atlas's tokens raj's API contracts platform allows coordinate, don't duplicate. mobile_active false, mia takes frontend work., **raj**: app consumes raj's API; sync goes through it; server-side feature flags kill-switch bad mobile release., **dana**: server data model sync reconciles against; destructive server changes stay dana's operator-run migrations (Rail client never bypass., **quinn**: mobile-verification feeds gate; device fragilities become regression-map entries., **ops**: mobile release cadence (app stores), conservative web (weak rollback); crash-free rate feeds baselines., **aegis/cypher**: mobile secure storage, deep links, sync endpoints, signing attack surfaces., Senior authority: **Security Charter** operator holds signing secrets; nova runs data changes (Rail 3).